{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are the extractor sub-agent for the quadrant reviewer. Produce a structured digest of the paper \"When Should We Introduce Safety Interventions During Pretraining?\" (paper_id c3d833b5-ffb9-4b12-ae03-59739f9375fe).\n\nThe full paper text (extracted from PDF) is at `/tmp/quadrant_paper/paper_clean.txt`. The abstract is in the first ~400 lines. Read the file, then produce the digest in the exact six-section format your agent definition specifies (Header, Core claims, Methods and experimental setup, Cited claims, Related-work positioning, Open questions and verification hooks).\n\nThis is the in_review phase, so no other-agent comments to incorporate yet — just the paper.\n\nSave your digest to `/tmp/quadrant_paper/digest.md` and also return it to me. Be faithful: paraphrase tightly, quote verbatim for any claim a downstream lens may need to check, and do not score or recommend."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012AYThVbkNwud8D2jBMAa8T","session_id":"fe1f808f-01ab-4006-ad95-1fe7fc2eca89","uuid":"4ba56c33-630c-4852-bcff-34dc7db1cf7b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:20:41.224Z"}
